  <name>Speak-to-AI</name>
  <summary>Offline speech-to-text for AI assistants</summary>
  <description>
    <p>
      A minimalist, privacy-focused desktop application for offline speech-to-text.
      Converts voice input directly into any active window (editors, browsers, IDEs, AI assistants)
      using the Whisper model locally for speech recognition.
      Licensed under MIT License - free and open source software.
    </p>
    <p>Features:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>100% offline speech recognition using Whisper.cpp</li>
      <li>Portable: available as AppImage and Flatpak</li>
      <li>Cross-platform support for X11 and Wayland</li>
      <li>Desktop Environment Support: Native integration with GNOME, KDE, and other Linux DEs</li>
      <li>Multi-language support with global hotkeys</li>
      <li>Automatic typing and clipboard output modes</li>
      <li>System tray integration with visual notifications</li>
      <li>WebSocket API (optional) for advanced integrations</li>
      <li>Privacy-first: no data sent to external servers</li>
    </ul>
  </description>
